          "buttonOnMobile": false,
          "label": "<p>Which of the following muscles does NOT converge on the perineal body?</p>",
          "x": 30,
          "y": 30,
          "width": 40,
          "height": 25,
          "libraryTitle": "Multiple Choice",
          "action": {
            "library": "H5P.MultiChoice 1.16",
            "params": {
              "question": "<p>Which of the following muscles does NOT converge on the perineal body?</p>",
              "answers": [
                {
                  "text": "<div>Bulbospongiosus</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Bulbospongiosus anchors on the perineal body in both sexes and is one of the key muscles converging on this central node.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>External anal sphincter</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The external anal sphincter attaches to the perineal body posteriorly and is one of several muscles that meet at this point.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Obturator internus</div>",
                  "correct": true,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Obturator internus lines the lateral wall of the ischiorectal fossa. The muscles converging on the perineal body are bulbospongiosus, external anal sphincter, transverse perinei (superficial and deep), and fibres of levator ani.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Deep transverse perinei</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Deep transverse perinei attaches to the perineal body from both sides and is one of the muscles giving this node its central supporting role.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                }
              ],
              "overallFeedback": [
                {
                  "from": 0,
                  "to": 50,
                  "feedback": "The perineal body receives bulbospongiosus, external anal sphincter, superficial and deep transverse perinei, and levator ani fibres. Obturator internus belongs to the lateral wall of the ischiorectal fossa."
                },
                {
                  "from": 51,
                  "to": 100,
                  "feedback": "Correct! Obturator internus forms the lateral wall of the ischiorectal fossa — it does not converge on the perineal body."
                }
              ],
